# üìö Docs or angular.io bug report

### Description

The documentation for [HostListener](https://angular.io/api/core/HostListener) doesn't mention what return type the method can have, nor it provides a link of clues about where to go to search for that information.

For example, when using the `HostListener` with a return value (like in [Angular's routerLink's source code](https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/master/packages/router/src/directives/router_link.ts)), we can return `true` or `false`, like this:
```
  @HostListener("click")
  onClick() {
    console.log("pressed");
    return false;
 }
```

There is no mention in that page about how the return type of the `onClick` method affects navigation (`false` prevents the default behaviour of an `a` link for example).

If adding this information is out of the scope for the `HostListener` documentation, at least a link to a list of events with more documentation would be appreciated in there, as this is the page where we go to search such information.




