### What's the affected URL?**
https://angular.io/api/core/HostListener

# üêû Bug report

### Command (mark with an `x`)
- [ ] new
- [x] build
- [ ] serve

### Description

fileReplacements for non TypeScript (JavaScript) files doesn't work with ng build. ng serve correctly replaces all files defined in angular.json as stated in angular [docs](https://angular.io/guide/build#configure-target-specific-file-replacements) ```The main CLI configuration file, angular.json, contains a fileReplacements section in the configuration for each build target, which allows you to replace ```**any**``` file with a target-specific version of that file.```

This feature is critical for our project because some of our scss, html and assets files are different per configuration.

In #19717 have been discussion about this being expected behavior. I don't agree because ng serve works correctly and docs state this should work for **any** file.

If you don't agree, please fix docs and provide us alternative solution to replace files at compile time.

